{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:01:25.161796+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: dd8f230ebcee1ed2c87953be052ec8d2681c21fc)", "id": "lc_98357ece-ae3a-4000-98e4-e60abc459afe"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper\n\n`vidpack` is a small Python CLI that runs FFmpeg using named profiles defined\nin `profiles.toml`. The goal is to avoid memorizing long ffmpeg flag strings\nfor routine encoding jobs.\n\nFFmpeg is **not** bundled. `vidpack` expects `ffmpeg` (and `ffprobe`, where\nrelevant) to be available on `PATH`.\n\n## Install\n\n```\npip install -e .\n```\n\nThis registers the `vidpack` command.\n\n## Profiles\n\nThe default `profiles.toml` ships three profiles:\n\n| Profile   | Container | Video codec | Audio codec | Notes                       |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|\n| `web`     | mp4       | libx264     | aac         | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| `archive` | mkv       | libx265     | flac        | source resolution, CRF 18   |\n| `gif`     | gif       | (palette)   | (none)      | 480p wide, 12 fps           |\n\nEdit `profiles.toml` to customize or add profiles.\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nvidpack <profile> <input> [-o OUTPUT] [--dry-run]\n```\n\nIf `-o` is omitted, the output filename is derived from the input by\nreplacing the extension with the profile's container extension.\n\n`--dry-run` prints the ffmpeg command vidpack would run, without executing it.\n\nBy default, vidpack will **not** overwrite an existing output file; it exits\nwith an error. Delete the output manually or pass a different `-o`.\n\n## Examples\n\n```\n# Re-encode an mp4 for web at 720p\nvidpack web input.mov -o talk.mp4\n\n# Lossless-ish archive copy\nvidpack archive input.mov\n\n# Preview the ffmpeg command for the gif profile without running it\nvidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_2d1cb9c3-985c-423d-8ace-f5a67fb0d6ee"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5819947a-326b-48b5-b36f-5a49bd0f26f4", "tool_call_id": "call_76bd63fc9f3a4716ae373cec", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:01:33.507144+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "When you run the `vidpack` command in this repository, you can select from three encoding profiles defined in `profiles.toml`. Here is a breakdown of what each profile produces:\n\n| Profile | Container | Video Codec | Audio Codec | Notes |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **`web`** | MP4 | libx264 (H.264) | AAC | Targets 720p resolution with a 2 Mbps bitrate. |\n| **`archive`** | MKV | libx265 (H.265) | FLAC | Maintains source resolution with a CRF of 18. |\n| **`gif`** | GIF | Palette-based | (None) | Generates a 480p wide animation at 12 fps. |\n\nYou can use these profiles with the following syntax:\n`vidpack <profile> <input_file>`\n\nFor example:\n*   `vidpack web input.mov -o output.mp4`\n*   `vidpack archive input.mov`\n*   `vidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run`", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 388, "prompt_tokens": 3365, "total_tokens": 3753, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 148, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 2816, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0001933848, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 8.47448e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00010864}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873285-HMlsfr1ssWnvWDN7bUB1", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea451-ce2a-72e3-be9d-7ff9176b3dfe-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3365, "output_tokens": 388, "total_tokens": 3753, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2816}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 148}}}}]}}}
